ho footwear market cimtlmici gen\nerally inilet, and oh yet Un cxcti\"d\nrevival of bulrtes following tno do\nparturo of buytrs from U Ilcxton\nmarket hn fulled to develop to nny,\ngreat oxtenf, tho demrmd bring Irreg\nular. Producers of niclalltie, par\nticularly cfoth f.Jri guodit, continue\nIn rcccl of rteody orders, while !an\ndanl lines aro goncruMy ncv?i-cicd.\nWeathtr Interferes.\nnrndatreot's letter nald-\nRetail trado ha loen hanrjK-rcd by\nwarm weather In tto Smrtli, Southwest\nand West, while snowstorms in ihc\nBast and Northwest deterred distribu\ntion, thus ncntlvlntr lh. designed ef\nfect of clcapjnoj n?Vrt. WJioIean'n\ntrade has Improved a llttlo In tlx\nSuuthwcbt more oneorful there. In\ndeed, than for n long tlmo post out\nbusiness as a wl.olo Is IneJcwnrd and\nbuyors who ar- now vKIUik; tbo cen\ntral markets aro purchasing coasorva\nUvoly. Fewer Business Failures.\nIIuhIih-ss failures In tho I'nltrd\nStates for the week ending February\n1G were 235, as compared with 2t)l Ins!\nweek and 2G3 In the corresponding\nweek of 1310. In Canada 31, as com\npared with 17 last week, and 'J5 In the\ncorresponding week last year.\nTho new discounts In tho leather tnido\nhave restricted trado uuitorially, cpw\ndaily In solo leather, where thoy haSe\nbeen put Into oimra'lon to Ui great\nest extent.\nI THE MARKETS f\nCincinnati Oram idarHet\nHour Winter jntwiut $I.S.\"o1.r.O,\ndo family $3 25a3.50. low grade JiCIa\n2.75, eprlni; patent j5.Cea!i.75, fun\nlly ll.8r.afi.2u. Wheat -No. 2 red tfo.i\nUllc, No. a red SCaSSe., No. 4 SCnSIc\nCorn No, whJto i 7 \"tat S 'Ac, No. .1\nwhite iCa471.ic, No 2 yellow 47!n\n48Hc, No. 3 yellow -KViU'fce. No.2\nmJxtd iii'.iaH'yic, No. 3 mixed 43 4a\n4C',4c. (Xits No. 2 Whllo V,ViiHr.r,\nstandard white 33n33Uc, No. 2 niixi1\n33 1,3 Ic.\nCincinnati Live Stock.\nCattle Shippers $5.25aC25. butcher\nsteers, extra JTi.Sr.aC, good to 0I10U0\n$5.25ari.7.r.; hetfem, extra $5.r.0a5.C0\ngood to choK'o l.8unG.40; cows, oxtr.t\n4.srarj, coed to ch